<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id785b58a8-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s602"><num value="602">§ 602.</num><heading> Seizure of timber cut</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">If any timber cut on the public lands shall be exported from the Territories of the United States, it shall be liable to seizure by United States authority wherever found.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id785b58a9-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/act/1878-04-30/ch76/s2">Apr. 30, 1878, ch. 76, § 2</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/20/46">20 Stat. 46</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
